---
import "@/styles/globals.css";
import Layout from "@/layouts/Layout.astro";
import PageHeading from "@/components/ui/PageHeading.astro";
import { Icon } from "astro-icon/components";
---

<Layout title="About">
  <section>
    <div class="dots py-14">
      <div class="layout">
        <PageHeading
          title="About"
          description="Learn a bit about me and the type of person I am."
        />
      </div>
    </div>

    <div class="layout mb-20 mt-10 flex flex-col space-y-10 lg:text-lg">
      <div class="flex flex-col space-y-5">
        <p>
          Hello! My name is Antonio Lopez. I'm a full-stack web developer based
          in Orange County, CA. I work in the React.js ecosystem using Next.js
          as my frontend framework of choice for complex projects but have
          recently taken a liking to Astro due to its flexibility and reduced
          reliance on Javascript. For expediting my styling process, I rely on
          the utility-first framework Tailwind CSS. My content management is
          streamlined with Sanity CMS, facilitating effortless CRUD operations.
          Figma serves as my preferred tool for prototyping and wireframes,
          contributing to the enhancement of my design skills.
        </p>
        <p>
          As for the backend, I've seamlessly worked with both REST and GraphQL
          APIs, employing Node.js, Express.js, and Next.js for consumption.
          Postman aids in testing and debugging routes, while storage is managed
          through MongoDB and Google's Firebase Firestore.
        </p>
        <p>
          When I'm not staring at my computer screen all day I like to drive to
          different cities and catch live band performances. I tend to lean
          towards punk genres, although it changes based on my mood. I frequent
          many craft breweries, hazy IPAs are my favorite. To maintain a
          balanced lifestyle I workout and weight lift. I also listen to
          podcasts, watch anime, and read manga. Got any recommendations? Let's
          grab a pint and have a chat!
        </p>
      </div>

      <div
        class="mt-5 flex items-center justify-center space-x-8 md:mt-8 md:justify-start"
      >
        <Icon
          name="github"
          width={32}
          height={32}
          title="antonio lopez github link"
          class="transition-colors hover:text-primary"
        />
        <Icon
          name="linkedin"
          width={32}
          height={32}
          title="antonio lopez linkedin link"
          class="transition-colors hover:text-primary"
        />
        <Icon
          name="envelope"
          width={32}
          height={32}
          title="antonio lopez email link"
          class="transition-colors hover:text-primary"
        />
      </div>

      <div class="grid grid-cols-2 gap-8 md:grid-cols-5 md:gap-0">
        <div>
          <p class="font-semibold">Frontend</p>
          <ul class="ml-8 mt-4 list-outside list-disc">
            <li>Next JS</li>
            <li>Astro</li>
            <li>React</li>
            <li>Typscript</li>
          </ul>
        </div>
        <div>
          <p class="font-semibold">Backend</p>
          <ul class="ml-8 mt-4 list-outside list-disc">
            <li>Sanity io</li>
            <li>Postman</li>
            <li>MongoDB</li>
            <li>Docker</li>
          </ul>
        </div><div>
          <p class="font-semibold">API</p>
          <ul class="ml-8 mt-4 list-outside list-disc">
            <li>GraphQL</li>
            <li>REST</li>
          </ul>
        </div><div>
          <p class="font-semibold">Stlying</p>
          <ul class="ml-8 mt-4 list-outside list-disc">
            <li>Tailwind CSS</li>
            <li>Figma</li>
            <li>Shadcn UI</li>
            <li>Storybook</li>
            <li>CSS 3</li>
          </ul>
        </div><div>
          <p class="font-semibold">Hosting</p>
          <ul class="ml-8 mt-4 list-outside list-disc">
            <li>Vercel</li>
            <li>Netlify</li>
            <li>Cloudinary</li>
          </ul>
        </div>
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>
</Layout>
